But the ritual of it, and the benefits of being in the room with opposing counsel and the judge, made it worth any moments of discomfort

This was a judicial review - technical analysis of case law from across the country. It was supplemented by good written material. It ran for just under two hours - an eternity on the phone.
I was sweating bullets because it was so hot and I was in a full suit. 3/4

There's a place for court by webcam. There's a place for court by phone. But being able to look at a judge, pause when they are looking for documents, and have back-and-forth discussions (which I've found much more difficult by phone) is key.

For the first time since March 2020 I was able to make oral submissions in a courtroom. I am the world's biggest advocate for using technology to make law more efficient, but nothing really compares to being in the same room as a Judge to present a case. 1/?
